Indexers are used for allowing the classes to be indexed like arrays. 
Indexers will resemble the property structure but only difference is indexerâ€™s accessors will take parameters. F
or example,

class MyCollection<T>
{
 private T[] myArr = new T[100];
 public T this[int t]
 {
 get
 {
 return myArr[t];
 }
 set
 {
 myArr[t] = value;
 }
 }
}
